## redis-cli Usage

### Installation

```bash
# Build from source (redis-cli only)
cd /path/to/redis-source && make redis-cli

# Or install full Redis
brew install redis   # macOS
apt install redis-tools  # Debian/Ubuntu

# Docker (no local install)
docker run -it --rm redis redis-cli -h <host> -p 6379
```

**Source**: [Redis CLI Installation](https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/tools/cli)

### Connection Options

| Option | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `-h <host>` | Host (default: 127.0.0.1) |
| `-p <port>` | Port (default: 6379) |
| `-a <password>` | Password (prefer `REDISCLI_AUTH` env var for security) |
| `-n <db>` | Database number (0–15 by default) |
| `-u redis://user:pass@host:port/db` | URI format |
| `--tls` | Enable SSL/TLS |
| `-4` / `-6` | Prefer IPv4 or IPv6 |

```bash
# Connect with password (use env var in scripts)
export REDISCLI_AUTH=mysecret
redis-cli -h redis.example.com -p 6379 PING

# URI format
redis-cli -u redis://user:p%40ssw0rd@host:6379/0 PING
```

### Output Modes

| Flag | Effect |
|------|--------|
| `--raw` | Raw output (no type prefixes like `(integer)`) |
| `--no-raw` | Human-readable when piping |
| `--csv` | CSV format for single command |

```bash
redis-cli INCR counter
(integer) 7

redis-cli --raw INCR counter
8
```

### Special Modes

```bash
# Run command N times with interval
redis-cli -r 5 -i 1 INCR counter

# Monitor commands in real time
redis-cli MONITOR

# Scan for big keys (avoid KEYS * in production)
redis-cli --bigkeys

# Memory usage per key
redis-cli --memkeys

# Pub/sub mode
redis-cli SUBSCRIBE channel
```

### Piping Commands

```bash
# From file
cat commands.txt | redis-cli

# From stdin (value)
redis-cli -x SET mykey < /path/to/file
```

### Lua Scripts

```bash
# Run script from file
redis-cli --eval /tmp/script.lua key1 key2 , arg1 arg2

# Keys and args separated by comma (space before comma)
redis-cli --eval script.lua location:hastings:temp , 23
```

