## Core Commands

### Strings

| Command | Complexity | Purpose |
|---------|------------|---------|
| `SET key value [EX seconds\|PX ms\|EXAT\|PXAT] [NX\|XX] [GET]` | O(1) | Set string; NX=only if not exists, XX=only if exists |
| `GET key` | O(1) | Get string |
| `MGET key [key ...]` | O(N) | Get multiple |
| `INCR key` / `DECR key` | O(1) | Atomic increment/decrement |
| `APPEND key value` | O(1) | Append to string |
| `GETRANGE key start end` | O(N) | Substring |

### Hashes

| Command | Complexity | Purpose |
|---------|------------|---------|
| `HSET key field value [field value ...]` | O(1) per pair | Set hash fields |
| `HGET key field` | O(1) | Get field |
| `HGETALL key` | O(N) | Get all fields (use HSCAN for large hashes) |
| `HINCRBY key field increment` | O(1) | Atomic increment |

### Lists

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `LPUSH key value [value ...]` | Prepend |
| `RPUSH key value [value ...]` | Append |
| `LRANGE key start stop` | Get range (0 -1 = all) |
| `LPOP key` / `RPOP key` | Remove and return |

### Keyspace

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `KEYS pattern` | **Avoid in production** — blocks server; use SCAN |
| `SCAN cursor [MATCH pattern] [COUNT n]` | Iterate keys safely |
| `EXISTS key [key ...]` | Check existence |
| `DEL key [key ...]` | Delete |
| `EXPIRE key seconds` | Set TTL |
| `TTL key` | Get remaining TTL |

### Diagnostics

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `INFO [section]` | Server info (server, memory, stats, replication) |
| `LATENCY DOCTOR` | Latency troubleshooting |
| `MEMORY DOCTOR` | Memory troubleshooting |
| `CONFIG GET *` | View configuration |
| `CONFIG SET param value` | Change config at runtime (where supported) |

**Source**: [Redis Commands](https://redis.io/docs/latest/commands/)

