## Performance Best Practices

### Pipelining

**Send multiple commands in batch** — reduces round-trip latency.

```bash
# Instead of N round-trips, send all at once
(echo -e "SET a 1\nSET b 2\nGET a"; sleep 0.1) | redis-cli
```

**Client libraries**: Use pipeline support (e.g., redis-py `pipe()`, go-redis `Pipeline()`).

**Source**: [Redis Pipelining](https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/using-commands/pipelining)

### Client Recommendations

- **Health checks** — Use `PING` periodically.
- **Timeouts** — Configure connection and command timeouts.
- **Retry with backoff** — go-redis defaults: 3 attempts, 8–512ms backoff.
- **Check errors** — Always validate command results before proceeding.

**Source**: [Redis Production Usage (Go)](https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/clients/go/produsage/), [Redis Production Usage (Python)](https://redis.io/docs/latest/develop/clients/redis-py/produsage/)

