## Anti-Patterns

### ❌ KEYS * in Production

```bash
# ❌ BAD: Blocks server, O(N) over entire keyspace
KEYS *

# ✅ GOOD: Non-blocking iteration
SCAN 0 MATCH user:* COUNT 100
```

### ❌ No maxmemory

```
❌ BAD: Redis grows until OOM or kernel kills process
✅ GOOD: Set maxmemory with eviction policy (e.g., allkeys-lru)
```

### ❌ Unauthenticated Redis

```
❌ BAD: Redis exposed without requirepass or ACL
✅ GOOD: requirepass, ACLs, network isolation
```

### ❌ SELECT in Connection Pool

```
❌ BAD: Multiple databases with shared connection pool (connection confusion)
✅ GOOD: One database per logical service, or separate pools per DB
```

